article.headline: Indiana State 71, Eastern Illinois 56
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- David Moss had 23 points as Indiana State defeated Eastern Illinois 71-56 on Saturday. Moss hit all 10 of his free throw attempts. Indiana State (2-2) also got contributions from Marcus Howard, who had 12 points and Eric Gray, who scored 10 points off the bench. David Roos led Eastern Illinois (0-4) with 15 points and five rebounds. Derrik Hollyfield added nine points and Josh Gomes has seven. The Panthers were successful on just four of their 17 3-point attempts. The Sycamores went on a 25-9 run to start the game and never trailed. Moss scored 15 of his points during that run. Indiana State pushed the lead as high as 21 after Tyson Schnitker hit a 3-pointer with 15:45 remaining. The Panthers shot just 39 percent from the field -- 26.7 percent in the first half -- while the Sycamores made 51 percent of their attempts. Indiana State also shot well from the free throw line, connecting on 91 percent of their attempts.
